stylometry: The relationship between price and demand is ultimately that price determines demand. Sort of like in our elasticity of demand - we can see that price determines demand as well. When setting the price of the product or service we must consider the target market - who we are setting the prices for, in other words who are our potential buyers/customers. We want to make sure that the price we set will match the quality we are offering. We also want to make sure the price is right, that way the cycle of consumers buying is greater - therefore we won't have much backorder, or stock; this will eliminate holding costs, etc. You can develop a model of price vs. demand and have a tradeoff table  within to help you find the best fit decision. In price vs. demand we ulitmately have the consumer in mind - for the product or service available to them.
